{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timezone\/init(identifier:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"title":"init(identifier:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"init","roleHeading":"Initializer","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">?)","kind":"text"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib8TimeZoneC10identifierACSPys4Int8VGSg_tcfc"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"init","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"identifier","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">? = nil)"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"text":" can either be an RFC3339\/ISO 8601 time offset or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"something that would pass as a valid value for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"type":"text","text":" environment"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variable (including "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In Windows, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be the unlocalized name of a time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"zone for standard time, for example “Pacific Standard Time”."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Valid RFC3339 time offsets are "},{"code":"\"Z\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (for UTC) or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"±hh:mm\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":".  ISO 8601 additionally specifies"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"\"±hhmm\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hh\""},{"text":".  Offsets are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"time values to be added to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) to get","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the local time."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In UNIX, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable typically corresponds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the name of a file in the zoneinfo database, an absolute path to a file"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"somewhere else, or a string in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"“std offset [dst [offset],start[\/time],end[\/time]]” (POSIX) format.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"There  are  no spaces in the specification. The name of standard","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and daylight savings time zone must be three or more alphabetic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"characters. Offsets are time values to be added to local time to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"get Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) and should be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"[±]hh[[:]mm[:ss]]\""},{"type":"text","text":".  Dates are either"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Jn\""},{"text":" (Julian day with n between 1 and 365, leap","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"years not counted), "},{"code":"\"n\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (zero-based Julian day"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with n between 0 and 365) or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Mm.w.d\""},{"type":"text","text":" (day d"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(0 <= d <= 6) of week w (1 <= w <= 5) of month m (1 <= m <= 12), day"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"0 is a Sunday).  Times are in local wall clock time, the default is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"02:00:00."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Windows, the “tzn[+|–]hh"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"#dzn","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"” format is used, but also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"accepts POSIX format.  The Windows format uses US rules for all time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"zones; daylight savings time is 60 minutes behind the standard time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with date and time of change taken from Pacific Standard Time."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Offsets are time values to be added to the local time to get","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_time_zone_new_local()"},{"type":"text","text":" calls this function with the value of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable. This function itself is independent of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the value of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"type":"text","text":", but if "},{"code":"identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" then "},{"code":"\/etc\/localtime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be consulted to discover the correct time zone on UNIX and the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"registry will be consulted or "},{"code":"GetTimeZoneInformation()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be used"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to get the local time zone on Windows."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If intervals are not available, only time zone rules from ","type":"text"},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"environment variable or other means, then they will be computed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"from year 1900 to 2037.  If the maximum year for the rules is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"available and it is greater than 2037, then it will followed"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instead.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"See","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for a precise definition of valid RFC3339 time offsets","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"code":"time-offset","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" expansion) and ISO 8601 for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"full list of valid time offsets.  See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for an explanation of the possible","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values of the "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the list of time zones on Windows."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should release the return value by calling "},{"code":"g_time_zone_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when you are done with it."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(identifier:)"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" corresponding to "},{"code":"identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"text":" cannot be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsed or loaded, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}],"references":{"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339#section-5.6":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RFC3339 §5.6"}],"type":"link","title":"RFC3339 §5.6","identifier":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6","url":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZone":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezone","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TimeZone","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"TimeZone","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZone"}]},"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Microsoft Time Zone Index Values"}],"type":"link","title":"Microsoft Time Zone Index Values","identifier":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx","url":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx"},"#dzn":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":":mm[:ss]"}],"type":"link","title":":mm[:ss]","identifier":"#dzn","url":"#dzn"},"http://www.gnu.org/s/libc/manual/html_node/TZ-Variable.html":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The GNU C Library manual"}],"type":"link","title":"The GNU C Library manual","identifier":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html","url":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZone/init(identifier:)":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezone\/init(identifier:)","title":"init(identifier:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(identifier:)","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">?)"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" corresponding to "},{"code":"identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" cannot be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsed or loaded, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}]}}}